@namespace ActualChat.Audio.UI.Blazor.Components

<img src="/dist/images/guide/mic-access.png" alt="mic access">
<div class="c-text text-title-1">
   Microphone access is blocked, but you can fix this!
</div>
<div class="c-text font-normal">
    Actual Chat requires microphone access to record and transcribe your messages.
    To enable it in Google Chrome:
</div>

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    1. Click "More" button in the upper right corner, and then click "Settings"
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-01.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/01">

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    2. Choose "Privacy and security" on the left side
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-02.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/02">

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    3. Select "Site settings"
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-03.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/03">

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    4. Select "Microphone"
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-04.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/04">

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    5. Check that you allow sites to ask to use your microphone
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-05.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/05">

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    6. If "actual.chat" is not allowed to use microphone, select it
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-06.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/06">

<div class="c-text text-headline-1">
    7. Change "Permissions" > "Microphone" value from "Deny" to "Allow" or "Ask"
</div>
<img src="/dist/images/guide/web-chrome-07.png" alt="WEB/Chrome/07">
